18 Jul 2015 Democratic Republic of Congo: DRC - Ituri: no Ebola epidemic in Niania - suspected case negative for Ebola and Marburg virus
https://flutrackers.com/forum/forum/africa/ebola-tracking-dem-republic-of-congo/735400-drc-ituri-no-ebola-epidemic-in-niania-suspected-case-negative-for-ebola-and-marburg-virus
[According to Dr. Louis Tshulo "The result has just reached us. The sample we sent from Niania hospital, where blood was taken from a suspected case who was bleeding, is negative to the Ebola virus and Marburg virus. There is no Ebola disease in Niania currently. I can confirm, and it is the result that comes from Kinshasa." The young man had been tested after presenting with bleeding from the nose, mouth, ears and skin. Blood samples were taken on 9 Jul 2015. The young man and his wife have been quarantined in Niania health zone. (Google translation)]

