[According to officials, an herbalist (who treated the index patient of Liberia's latest outbreak of Ebola virus disease) has escaped quarantine and fled to Nimba County. The index patient is a 17-year-old-boy from the village of Nedowian, in Margibi County. Nimba County is in north Liberia, near Guinea. The herbalist is one of 120 people placed under quarantine for coming into contact with the deceased index patient.

According to Paul Karnue, spokesperson for the Nimba local government, "The herbalist evaded quarantine and is on the run; this is a reason we are putting everybody on alert. Nimba County authorities are not taking Ebola's recurrence lightly because the county suffered severely during the 1st outbreak. According to Karnue: "It is worth mentioning that the 1st Ebola case in Nimba County in 2014 started with a similar story. One herbalist went to Monrovia to treat an Ebola patient, where he contracted the virus and returned with it to Nimba. This is how Ebola spread and took away the lives of hundreds of citizens." ]

