16 Jul 2015 Sierra Leone: Ebola burial teams seek bribes in Sierra Leone: health official
http://www.reuters.com/article/2015/07/16/us-health-ebola-leone-idUSKCN0PQ1L420150716?rpc=401
[According to Palo Conteh, head of the National Ebola Response Center, Ebola burial teams are soliciting bribes from the families of the dead for the performance of safe burials. Some burial teams are demanding nearly SLL 1 million (USD 247) from the families for safe burial services for the deceased. This has produced an increase in illegal burials.

On Wed 15 Jul 2015, Mr. Conteh, told reporters of allegations that Connaught Hospital burial teams had demanded bribes for safe burial services, and were being investigated.

In addition, Sierra Leone's Parliament has adopted recommendations by its Public Accounts Committee (PAC) to suspend 3 government officials for charges of violating procurement rules in the management of Ebola funds. Sierra Leone's auditor said in February 2015 the government had not produced a full accounting for nearly 1/3rd of the USD 20 million meant for fighting the Ebola virus disease.]

[It is a disgrace that money donated to protect the general population and health care workers from infection with Ebola virus is being misused, jeopardizing everyone's health. - Mod.LK]

