15 Jul 2015 Japan Ensures Vital Support to Ebola Survivors
http://news.sl/drwebsite/publish/article_200527927.shtml
[The United Nations World Food Programme (WFP) welcomes Japan's donation of USD 6 million to support WFP's response in Ebola-affected Sierra Leone, including support to some 3000 Ebola survivors across the country. ...

As part of its Ebola response, WFP ensures that survivors' food and nutritional needs are met as they return home to their communities and pick up their jobs and lives. Survivors receive a one-month package of rice, beans, oil, and a nutritious corn-soya blend.

WFP is also implementing a mobile cash transfer programme to provide two additional months of support to survivors, to allow them to purchase their own foods in local markets. This gives survivors more choice over the food they eat while boosting local markets, some of which were closed for months due to the Ebola outbreak and movement restrictions. ... - more]

